Nigeria Population to Hit 166 Million by October, Guardian Says

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-07-12T08:28:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-12/nigeria-population-to-hit-166-million-by-october-guardian-says.html
Nigeria’s population will reach 166
million by the end of October, the  Guardian  reported, citing
Samu’ila Makama, chairman of the National Population Commission.  The population was 140 million in 2006 and is growing at
3.2 percent per annum, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 